{"lemma":"مَعْقِلٌ","slug":"مَعْقِلٌ","root":"ع.ق.ل","root_slug":"ع-ق-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ق-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29997"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%82%D9%90%D9%84%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"refuge, sanctuary"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"stronghold, citadel, bastion, fortress, fortification"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the root ع ق ل (ʕ q l)."},"ipa":["/maʕ.qil/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29997","headword_ar":"مَعْقِلٌ","root":"Eql","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place to which one betakes himself for refuge, protection, preservation, covert,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"malojaA^N","text_ar":"مَلْجَاٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, O, Msb, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) of which the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuquwlN","text_ar":"عُقُولٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) but Az says that he had not heard"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaqol","text_ar":"عَقْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this sense on any authority except that of Lth; and held"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuquwlu","text_ar":"العُقُولُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is cited as an ex. of its pl., to signify “ the protecting oneself in a mountain: ” (TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEoqilN","text_ar":"مَعْقِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fortress;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaqolN","text_ar":"عَقْلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is said to do;] syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiSonN","text_ar":"حِصْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqilu","text_ar":"مَعَاقِلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) Hence one says, using it metaphorically,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa maEoqilu qawomihi","text_ar":"هُوَ مَعْقِلُ قَوْمِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is the refuge of his people:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the kings of Himyer are termed in a trad."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqilu AlA^aroDi","text_ar":"مَعَاقِلُ الاَرْضِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The fortresses"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refuges"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the land."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  [It is perhaps primarily used in relation to camels; for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEaAqilu AlA_ibili","text_ar":"مَعَاقِلُ الاـِبِلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The places in which the camels are bound with the rope called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiqaAl","text_ar":"عِقَال"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}